It is with deep regret that we inform you about a recent loss to the Rosedale Union School District and the Almondale Elementary School Community. Leilah Johnson, a sixth-grade student, passed away in a tragic drowning accident while on a family vacation in Oklahoma. Our thoughts and sympathies are with her family and friends during this unspeakable time.

Information regarding the funeral services will be made available at a later date.

post_text:
We are excited to announce that phase two of the P-EBT process in California began May 22, 2020. Families with children who are eligible for Free or Reduced-Price meals that have not yet received a P-EBT card in the mail, can now apply for P-EBT benefits online at http://www.ca.p-ebt.org/.
You must apply online no later than June 30, 2020.

What this means is, that if you have turned in a paper application or completed an online application and you were approved for free or reduced lunches through OUR school district you may be eligible for this program through the State of California. If you are unsure, please email Mary Anne at mgroves@ruesd.net and she will be glad to check your status.

post_text:
Dear Rosedale Families,

During a time when there are more questions than answers about COVID-19, the Rosedale Union School District leadership team is planning for all kinds of possibilities for the return to school in the fall of 2020.

Will students return on staggered schedules to accommodate the need for social distancing?

Will teaching be a hybrid of distance and in-person learning?

Will some prefer only distance learning?

How might social distancing requirements influence transportation and school lunch programs?

As you might imagine, it is an incredibly complex and constantly changing environment. As part of that process, RUSD wants to hear from parents and community members so that we can best meet your individual needs.

Please take a moment to fill out this short survey by May 27th.

Fall 2020 Parent Survey

https://forms.gle/dTWezfZX1odUvtBJA

Thank you in advance for your input and know we will likely reach out in the coming weeks for additional feedback.

Respectfully,

Sue Lemon

District Superintendent

Dear Rosedale Families,

During a time when there are more questions than answers about COVID-19, the Rosedale Union School District leadership team is planning for all kinds of possibilities for the return to school in the fall of 2020.

Will students return on staggered schedules to accommodate the need for social distancing?

Will teaching be a hybrid of distance and in-person learning?

Will some prefer only distance learning?

How might social distancing requirements influence transportation and school lunch programs?

As you might imagine, it is an incredibly complex and constantly changing environment. As part of that process, RUSD wants to hear from parents and community members so that we can best meet your individual needs.

Please take a moment to fill out this short survey by May 27th.

Fall 2020 Parent Survey

https://forms.gle/dTWezfZX1odUvtBJA

Thank you in advance for your input and know we will likely reach out in the coming weeks for additional feedback.

Respectfully,

Sue Lemon

District Superintendent

post_text:
This is an important message from Rosedale Union School District. Pandemic E B T debit cards are being automatically mailed to families of children who receive Cal Fresh, Cal Works, Medi Cal or other social services. If you are eligible, you may receive up to $365.00 per child to help feed your family due to the COVID 19 school closure. Please keep an eye out for this card in the mail over the next few weeks. Families who qualify for Free and Reduced lunches via a paper application on an online application and have not received a card in the mail by May 22, 2020 you will need to complete a simple online application before June 30, 2020. Here is the web address: ca.p-ebt.org/?locale=en
As more information becomes available, we will be sure to pass it along.
